<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4456] openConnection().getContentLengthLong() always returns -1 for bundle URLs on Java7</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4456</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Java7 introduced a new method to URLConnection called getContentLengthLong. Felix&apos;s URLHandlersBundleURLConnection only overrides getContentLength, so the default getContentLengthLong implementation is left in place and always returns -1 for &apos;bundle&apos; URLs when running Felix on Java7.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The client-side workaround is to fall-back to getContentLength whenever getContentLengthLong returns -1, but it would be great if this could be fixed in a future framework release.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
